    <field id="description" text-type="text/html">&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: 12.800000190734863px; line-height: normal;"&gt;Query Builder enables the user to build complex queries visually&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;img src="attachment:querybuilder.jpg"/&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;ul style=""&gt;&lt;li style=""&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: 12.800000190734863px; line-height: normal;"&gt;It is possible to switch between query builder and the query language itself&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li style=""&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: 12.800000190734863px; line-height: normal;"&gt;The query language itself can be extended using custom macros&lt;br style=""/&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li style=""&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: 12.800000190734863px; line-height: normal;"&gt;Queries are cached for later reuse&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li style=""&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: 12.800000190734863px; line-height: normal;"&gt;Queries could be stored as global-, project  or user-related query. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li style=""&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: 12.800000190734863px; line-height: normal;"&gt;There are a number of default saved queries which are available using the drop down menu in the user interface.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;img src="attachment:queryoptions.jpg"/&gt;</field>
